question: Question: Pirate William Dampier was one of the first Europeans to see this Australian animal, which is scientifically known as C. atratus. For 10 points each: [10] Name this animal that, while not a raven, was the subject of an argument in The Logic of Scientific Discovery about the problems in "inferring universal statements from singular ones."
